"""
PDF -> DOCX Converter  |  Priority-Based Overflow Compression  v15-fixed
=========================================================================

KEY FIXES OVER v15-improved
----------------------------

FIX 1 — PAGE-OBJECT LIFETIME BUG
  pdfplumber Page objects become invalid once the `with pdfplumber.open()`
  context closes.  All floor-derivation calls that need a page object now
  happen INSIDE a single persistent pdfplumber session.

FIX 2 — AVAILABLE_PT CALCULATION
  The DOCX `available_pt` (usable body height) was mixing PDF margin data
  with DOCX margin data inconsistently, producing values that were either
  too large (overflow never triggered) or too small (over-compression).
  Now:
    available_pt = page_h_pt  - max(docx_top, pdf_top) - max(docx_bot, pdf_bot)
  with a guaranteed positive fallback.

FIX 3 — GEO ASSIGNMENT BEFORE PARAMS DERIVATION
  Sections need their `.geo` assigned before `_derive_page_params` is
  called, because params depend on geo.  The parse_sections → assign-geo
  → assign-params ordering is now explicit and correct.

FIX 4 — MAIN / FIX_OVERFLOW WIRING
  `fix_overflow` no longer accepts `pdf_footers` (footer code is commented
  out).  `main()` is updated to match.  The `pdfplumber` session for page
  objects is opened once at the top of `fix_overflow` and kept alive for
  the entire compression pass.

FIX 5 — OVERFLOW DETECTION GUARD
  Added a minimum-overflow threshold (1 pt) so tiny floating-point
  discrepancies don't trigger unnecessary compression.

FIX 6 — SECTION COUNT MISMATCH HANDLING
  When pdf2docx produces fewer sections than PDF pages (common for
  single-section documents), the reconciler now distributes geo objects
  more robustly so every section gets a valid PageGeometry.

COMPRESSION LOGIC — unchanged from v15-improved
------------------------------------------------
  Tier 0  Materialize implicit line spacing
  Tier 1  Paragraph spacing  — greedy, largest first
  Tier 2  Above-single line spacing — greedy, most-spaced first
  Tier 3  Below-single to dynamic floor — greedy, most-headroom first
  Tier R  Residual drain (≤ 2 pt remaining)
  Tier 4  Physical scale (last resort)
  Tier 5  Redistribute slack after resolution
"""

